# Stylesheets (`**/styles/**/*.css`)

## Tailwind v4
- Prefer **`@import 'tailwindcss'`** and project **`@layer`** order that matches **Clerk** / third-party docs (layer conflicts break resets and components).
- Use **`@source`** / **`@theme`** per current **Tailwind v4** docs when adding content paths or design tokens—avoid legacy `tailwind.config` assumptions unless the repo still uses them.

## Third-party widgets (RealScout, etc.)
- **CSS variables** on web components (`realscout-*`) should stay **readable** (contrast) and aligned with brand—document why colors differ from Tailwind tokens.
- Do not strip widget variables without testing the embed in browser.

## Custom CSS
- Prefer **Tailwind utilities** for layout/spacing; use custom classes for **keyframes**, **print**, or **vendor** overrides.
- Keep **specificity** low—avoid `!important` wars with Tailwind utilities.

## Performance
- Large unused CSS is less of an issue with Tailwind’s compiler, but **avoid** duplicating huge blocks across files.
